# rstudio_server
# wrapper functions and bash completion for /usr/sbin/rstudio-server
# requires: jq, mlr, ldapwhois (for display name resolution)
# must run as root or a user with sudo access to /usr/sbin/rstudio-server
#
# example:  rstudio_active_sessions
#           rstudio-server kill-session <TAB>
#           rstudio-server lock-user <TAB>
#
# NOTE: the following subcommands are confirmed non-functional on this installation:
#   suspend-session, suspend-all, force-suspend-session, force-suspend
